  "prompt": "Why was Sundar Pichai chosen as the CEO of Google?",
  "response": "Sundar Pichai was chosen as the CEO of Google due to his extensive experience, leadership skills, and significant contributions to the company over the years. He joined Google in 2004 and quickly proved himself with his work on Google Toolbar and later Google Chrome, which became one of the most popular web browsers worldwide. Pichai also led product management and innovation efforts for various Google products, including Gmail and Google Maps, showcasing his capability to drive successful projects.\n\nHis ability to manage teams, his deep understanding of technology, and his strategic vision were key factors that positioned him as a suitable leader for Google. When Larry Page and Sergey Brin, the co-founders of Google, decided to restructure and form Alphabet Inc. as the parent company, they appointed Sundar Pichai as the CEO of Google in 2015. This decision enabled them to focus more on other ventures under Alphabet while allowing Pichai to steer Google in continuing its growth and innovation.",
